= Part II: Battle at Sea

*Force and Dynamics in 1 Dimension*  
+ Using $v^2 = v_0^2 + 2a(x - x_0)$:  
   $25.0^2 = 0 + 2a(2.0)$  
   $a = \frac{25.0^2}{2(2.0)} = 156.25 \, \text{m/s}^2$.  

+ Average force: $F = ma = (10.0)(156.25) = 1562.5 \, \text{N}$.  

+ Cannon recoil force: $F = 1562.5 \, \text{N}$. Recoil acceleration: $a = \frac{F}{m} = \frac{1562.5}{200.0} = 7.81 \, \text{m/s}^2$.

