= Part III: The Treasure Island

*Dynamics in 2 Dimensions*  
+ Horizontal force: $F_x = F \cos \theta = 200 \cos 30^\circ = 173.2 \, \text{N}$.  
  Vertical force: $F_y = F \sin \theta - F_g = 200 \sin 30^\circ - (50.0)(9.8) = -240.0 \, \text{N}$.  

+ Friction force: $F_f = \mu F_n = (0.1)(50.0 \cdot 9.8 + 200 \sin 30^\circ) = 54.0 \, \text{N}$.  

+ Net force: $F_{net} = F_x - F_f = 173.2 - 54.0 = 119.2 \, \text{N}$.  

+ Acceleration: $a = \frac{F_{net}}{m} = \frac{119.2}{50.0} = 2.38 \, \text{m/s}^2$.  

+ Distance: $x = v_0t + \frac{1}{2}at^2 = 0 + \frac{1}{2}(2.38)(10.0)^2 = 119.0 \, \text{m}$.  

