*Impulse and Momentum*  
+ Final velocity: $p = mv$, $\Delta p = (1.0 + 3.0)v - (1.0)(6.0)$.  
   $\Delta p = 0 \implies (4.0)v = 6.0 \implies v = 1.5 \, \text{m/s}$.  

+ Average force: $\Delta p = F \Delta t$, $F = \frac{\Delta p}{\Delta t} = \frac{6.0 - (1.5 \cdot 4.0)}{0.5} = 12.0 \, \text{N}$.  

