= Part V: Celebration!

*Energy Conservation*  
+ Speed: $KE = PE$, $\frac{1}{2}mv^2 = mgh$, $v = \sqrt{2gh} = 7.67 \, \text{m/s}$.  

+ With resistance: $KE - W = \frac{1}{2}mv^2$, solving gives $v = 7.49 \, \text{m/s}$.  

*Uniform Circular Motion*  
+ Speed: $v = \frac{2 \pi r}{T} = \frac{2 \pi (2.5)}{3.0} = 5.24 \, \text{m/s}$.  

+ Tension: $F = \frac{mv^2}{r} = \frac{(25.0)(5.24)^2}{2.5} = 274.3 \, \text{N}$.  

+ Max speed: Solving $\frac{(25.0)v^2}{2.5} = 500$ gives $v = 7.07 \, \text{m/s}$.  

